<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-03-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Targeted adaptive isolation strategy for Covid-19 pandemic</TITLE><BODY>We investigate the effects of social distancing in controlling the impact of the Covid-19 epidemic using a simple SIR epidemic model. We show that an alternative or complementaryapproach based on targeted isolation of the vulnerable subpopulation may provide a moreefficient and robust strategy at a lower economic and social cost within a shorter timeframe.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>